#{127}{}{It's a military base in the northeast. I once spent a lot of time rummaging through the old houses there. Dangerous place. It has always been a little dangerous due to the rodents and robots. Doubly dangerous now, because of the prospectors, who are ravaging the army reserves for more than a year now. There are always wars between different gangs marauding the place.}
{127}{}{它是东北部的一个军事基地。我曾经花了很多时间翻找那里的老房子。危险的地方。由于有啮齿动物和机器人，它总是有点危险。现在更加危险了，因为探矿者们，他们正在蹂躏一年多的陆军预备队。抢劫这个地方的帮派之间总是有战争。 -- It's a military base in the northeast. I once spent a lot of time rummaging through the old houses there. Dangerous place. It has always been a little dangerous due to the rodents and robots. Doubly dangerous now, because of the prospectors, who are ravaging the army reserves for more than a year now. There are always wars between different gangs marauding the place.}
#{128}{}{In the south-east is a highway, but the nearest village in the direction is a long way off. Some particularly desperate caravans are trying to master this trade route and travel between Las Vegas and New Reno, but not many manage to survive the journey.}
{128}{}{东南方向有一条高速公路，但最近的村庄离这里很远。一些特别绝望的商队正试图掌握这条贸易路线，并在拉斯维加斯和新雷诺之间旅行，但没有多少人能够在这段旅程中幸存下来。 -- In the south-east is a highway, but the nearest village in the direction is a long way off. Some particularly desperate caravans are trying to master this trade route and travel between Las Vegas and New Reno, but not many manage to survive the journey.}
#{129}{}{What else?}
{129}{}{还有什么？ -- What else?}
#{130}{}{To the south and southwest of the mountains there is only desert. It's a harsh place. It17s impossible to live there, let alone travel, nobody even tries anymore. I don17t remember a single case of anyone ever making it from the south. Could there be any life beyond the desert? I doubt it.}
{130}{}{山脉的南部和西南部只有沙漠。这是个艰苦的地方。在那里生活是不可能的，更不用说旅行了，甚至没有人再尝试了。我不记得有人从南方来过。沙漠之外还有生命吗？我怀疑。 -- To the south and southwest of the mountains there is only desert. It's a harsh place. It17s impossible to live there, let alone travel, nobody even tries anymore. I don17t remember a single case of anyone ever making it from the south. Could there be any life beyond the desert? I doubt it.}
#{131}{}{Between us and the desert in the south, there are some highlands. Sometimes I go there for hunting, but never far in the mountains - I do not want to meet the local tribe that lives there.}
{131}{}{在我们和南方沙漠之间，有一些高地。有时我去那里打猎，但从不在山上走远――我不想见到住在那里的当地部落。 -- Between us and the desert in the south, there are some highlands. Sometimes I go there for hunting, but never far in the mountains - I do not want to meet the local tribe that lives there.}
#{132}{}{Tell me about the tribe in the south.}
{132}{}{告诉我南方的部落。 -- Tell me about the tribe in the south.}
#{133}{}{Those savages have almost forgotten how to speak. The entire tribe has probably been isolated  from the outside world since the days of the Great War. So, they have forced to inbreed with their relatives. I also know that they are cannibals. The shaking syndrome and gnawed human bones in the parking lots can prove that. How do I know? It happened. I saw it. A couple of times I even had to fight with them. They fight like animals, but what can they do with their clubs and spears against my rifle?}
{133}{}{那些野蛮人几乎忘了怎么说话。整个部落可能从大战时期起就与外界隔绝了。因此，他们被迫与亲戚近亲繁殖。我也知道他们是食人族。摇晃综合症和停车场啃人骨头可以证明这一点。我怎么知道？事情发生了。我看到了。有几次我甚至不得不和他们打架。他们像动物一样战斗，但他们能用棍棒和长矛对付我的步枪吗？ -- Those savages have almost forgotten how to speak. The entire tribe has probably been isolated  from the outside world since the days of the Great War. So, they have forced to inbreed with their relatives. I also know that they are cannibals. The shaking syndrome and gnawed human bones in the parking lots can prove that. How do I know? It happened. I saw it. A couple of times I even had to fight with them. They fight like animals, but what can they do with their clubs and spears against my rifle?}
#{140}{}{I have nothing against their way of life, but they shouldn17t impose their laws on ordinary people! We didn17t call them here. When there was only a couple of bikers in Bridgeport, it did not create any problems, but now they are starting to push us. A little more - and our lovely town will quickly become a war zone.}
{140}{}{我并不反对他们的生活方式，但是他们不应该把他们的法律强加给普通人！我们没有叫他们来。当布里奇波特只有几个车手的时候，这并没有造成任何问题，但现在他们开始推动我们。再多一点――我们可爱的小镇很快就会变成战区。 -- I have nothing against their way of life, but they shouldn17t impose their laws on ordinary people! We didn17t call them here. When there was only a couple of bikers in Bridgeport, it did not create any problems, but now they are starting to push us. A little more - and our lovely town will quickly become a war zone.}
#{141}{}{What do they want here?}
{141}{}{他们想在这里干什么？ -- What do they want here?}
#{142}{}{That's what I have no idea about. I have heard them talking and they seem to only have a vague idea themselves. They probably smelled trouble, they just don't know what.}
{142}{}{这就是我不知道的。我听到他们说话，他们自己似乎只有一个模糊的想法。他们可能闻到了麻烦，只是不知道是什么。 -- That's what I have no idea about. I have heard them talking and they seem to only have a vague idea themselves. They probably smelled trouble, they just don't know what.}
#{143}{}{They say you're trying to fix the electricity in the city. How is it going so far?}
{143}{}{他们说你在修城里的电。到目前为止进展如何？ -- They say you're trying to fix the electricity in the city. How is it going so far?}
#{144}{}{I lack the skills and time to deal with this issue. Why? You can help? Mind you, we have nothing to pay for your services.}
