#{147}{}{Listen. In the garage across the street there is a backup generator. It's in working condition, but I was not able to establish the supply of electricity to houses. Apparently, I'm a bad electrician. How to fix it? I don17t know. You have to look all over the town, check the switchboards, dig into the transformer, and deal with corrosion. If you17re a good technician and smart enough, you17ll fix it in no time.}
{147}{}{听。在街对面的车库里有一台备用发电机。它在工作状态，但我无法建立电力供应的房子。显然，我是个差劲的电工。如何修复？我不知道。你必须环顾全城，检查配电盘，挖掘变压器，处理腐蚀。如果你是一个好的技术员，足够聪明，你会很快修好的。 -- Listen. In the garage across the street there is a backup generator. It's in working condition, but I was not able to establish the supply of electricity to houses. Apparently, I'm a bad electrician. How to fix it? I don17t know. You have to look all over the town, check the switchboards, dig into the transformer, and deal with corrosion. If you17re a good technician and smart enough, you17ll fix it in no time.}
